gzippy (0.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * New: gzippy --analyze FILE prints a compression fingerprint —
    entropy, LZ77 coverage, match-length and back-reference-distance
    histograms, and a one-line verdict.
  * New: man pages ship with the package — gzippy(1), gzippy-format(5),
    gzippy-tuning(7).
  * No breaking changes; every existing flag still behaves the same.

 -- Jack Danger <github@jackdanger.com>  Fri, 24 Apr 2026 09:32:02 -0700

gzippy (0.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.
  * Parallel gzip compression using custom scheduler and zlib-ng
  * Fast decompression using libdeflate
  * Drop-in gzip replacement with compatible CLI
  * Optional gzippy-replace-gzip package for system-wide replacement

 -- Jack Danger <github@jackdanger.com>  Sun, 18 Jan 2026 12:00:00 -0800
